cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is about improving object recognition using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new method for combining two ResNet improvements, which involves stochastic depth and pyramid structure, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on CIFAR-100, which is a common dataset used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision.
